1 elud e such peace officer, is guilty of a misdemeanor. The peace
2 officer, while attempting to stop a violator of this section, may
3 communicate a request for the assistance of other peace officers
4 from any office, department or agency. Any peace officer within
5 this state having knowledge of such request is authorized to render
6 such assistance in stopping the violator and may effect an arrest
7 under this section upon probable cause. Violation of this
8 subsection shall constitute a misdemeanor and shall be punishable by
9 not more than one (1) year imprisonment in the county jail, or by a
10 fine of not less than One Hundred Dollars ($100.00) nor more than
11 Two Thousand Dollars ($2,000.00), or by both such fine and
12 imprisonment. A second or subsequent violation of this subsection
13 shall be punishable by not more than one (1) year in the county
14 jail, or by a fine of not less than Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00)
15 nor more than Five Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00), or both such fine
16 and imprisonment.
17 B. Any person who violates the provisions of subsection A of
18 this section in such manner as to endanger any other person shall be
19 deemed guilty of a felony punishable by imprisonment in the State
20 Penitentiary custody of the Department of Corrections for a term of
21 not less than one (1) year nor more than five (5) years, or by a
22 fine of not less than One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00) nor more than
23 Five Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00), or by both such fine and
24 imprisonment.
